, and at that time Crawfords, you had to stand in a big group outside. You weren't just called in - just stand in a big group outside and Mr Owen was then - he'd - he'd come out and he'd look at them all and he said, you, you, you, you, you, step over her
e
 - over this other side and then you were taken in and then when he found out - he asked you - where you lived and - would you be able to get to work in time, of course I lived all the way up in Everton. He said oh yes, will you be able to get to work on 
time? I said yes. And I used to walk then from Everton right down to Edgehill. There was no cars then, no buses, we never bothered with - just walked through - it was quicker then - we didn't mind it being kids like that.
